  "notes": "The ubiquity of AI across the organization requires a rethinking of skill-building initiatives. \nFrom leadership to IT to dev to line-of-business users, everyone in the organization plays an essential role in AI adoption. \nSimply upskilling the IT team is no longer enough; to help develop, deploy, and make use of new AI solutions, organizations must upskill their entire workforce in AI. \nBy taking a skills-first approach to data and AI, you can empower your business leaders to have the knowledge to design effective AI strategies, provide your technical teams with the skills to prepare your IT systems and build powerful AI solutions, and equip business users to put AI into action with their daily tasks.\n\nPRESENTER NOTES: See hidden slides in appendix for more examples of commercial skilling benefits"
}